N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 ยง 346.7 - Advertising

State Regulations

All rules and procedures of the chairman, relative to
advertising by a physician as set forth in section
325-1.16
of this Title are made
applicable to chiropractors, to the extent that they are not inconsistent with
the provisions of section 13-1 of the Workers' Compensation Law and the other
provisions duly promulgated thereunder. Notes
